# The Cardano network this instance runs against: mainnet, preprod or preview.
#
# It picks the Koios endpoint AND the explorer links, so a committee practising
# on a testnet is on that testnet everywhere — not merely in the data, with its
# explorer links still quietly pointing at mainnet.
#
# An unrecognised name is a startup error, never a silent fall back to mainnet:
# an operator who meant to practise and quietly ended up on mainnet would be
# voting for real.
#
# SanchoNet is NOT supported — it was the pre-Chang governance testnet and Koios
# does not serve it. Governance is live on preprod, which has a real 14-seat
# Constitutional Committee and a full set of test governance actions.
# CELLA_NETWORK=mainnet

# Cella configuration — every value is optional; sensible defaults are built in.
# Copy to .env and adjust as needed (or just export these in your shell).

# Path to the SQLite database file (created on first run).
CELLA_DB=cella.db

# Web server listen address.
CELLA_ADDR=:8080

# Override the Koios endpoint CELLA_NETWORK would choose. Only needed for a
# private or self-hosted Koios instance.
# KOIOS_URL=

# Optional Koios bearer token for higher rate limits (not required).
# KOIOS_TOKEN=

# Signs the session cookies that carry a delegate's identity. Leave it unset and
# Cella generates a random key at startup — secure, but sessions are dropped on
# every restart. Set it to a long random string for any persistent deployment,
# and keep it secret: anyone holding it can mint a session as any delegate.
# CELLA_SECRET=

# Enables the entry splash's roster picker, which signs a visitor in as whichever
# delegate they click — with NO proof of identity at all. It exists to demo the
# chamber without wallets.
#
# NEVER set this on an instance anyone else can reach. With it on, a stranger can
# vote in a delegate's name and author the committee's rationale, which is then
# anchored on-chain and cited permanently. Leave it unset and delegates sign in
# with a Cardano wallet.
# CELLA_DEMO=1

# Who this Cella instance belongs to: the path to a body JSON file.
#
# A Constitutional Committee seat may be held by a consortium of delegates or by
# a single member — both are common, and Cella handles either. The file names the
# body, its members and their wallet addresses (which is how Cella recognises them
# at sign-in), and its logo, which sits as a file ALONGSIDE the JSON.
#
# See body/curia.json for a worked consortium, body/solo.example.json for a single
# member. Copy one, edit it, point CELLA_BODY at it.
#
# Left unset, Cella uses the Cardano Curia body built into the binary.
# CELLA_BODY=body/curia.json

# The script address holding the committee's hot NFT. Its inline datum names the
# voting group — the delegates whose signatures the chain will accept on the
# committee's vote — and therefore what quorum actually is.
#
# Cella reads this from the chain rather than trusting local config, because the
# validator, not Cella, decides whether a vote transaction is accepted. Without
# it Cella says quorum is unknown rather than guessing.
# CELLA_HOT_NFT_ADDR=
